Drop cuda.txt deps that are not packaged in nixpkgs and that vLLM either
imports lazily (with a graceful fallback) or doesn't need on our path:

  - tilelang: only used by DeepSeek V4's mhc.py (Multi-Head Coalesced).
    We don't run DeepSeek V4 — its top-level import is lazy.
  - fastsafetensors: weight_utils.py wraps the import in try/except and
    substitutes a PlaceholderModule on ImportError.
  - nvidia-cutlass-dsl + quack-kernels: FlashAttention 4 cute-DSL path
    only. We use FlashAttention 3 via the vendored vllm_flash_attn build.

flashinfer-cubin and nvidia-cudnn-frontend stay in cuda.txt — both are
already covered by `pythonRemoveDeps` in the package definition.

diff --git a/requirements/cuda.txt b/requirements/cuda.txt
--- a/requirements/cuda.txt
+++ b/requirements/cuda.txt
@@ -12,14 +12,6 @@ torchvision==0.26.0 # Required for phi3v processor. See https://github.com/pytor
 flashinfer-python==0.6.8.post1
 flashinfer-cubin==0.6.8.post1
 apache-tvm-ffi==0.1.9
-tilelang==0.1.9
